                            <comment id="476766" author="adilger" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2025 18:42:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Based on comments in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38028&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38028&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13241&quot; title=&quot;mount.lustre for large filesystem runs slow debugfs commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: covert to libext2fs for rest of ldiskfs ops&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) it appears the &lt;tt&gt;dnode_init()&lt;/tt&gt; function in e2fsprogs &lt;tt&gt;lib/support/dict.c&lt;/tt&gt; is causing a symbol clash with an identically-named function in libzfs.  Since we already modify &lt;tt&gt;lib/support&lt;/tt&gt; in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38027&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38027&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13241&quot; title=&quot;mount.lustre for large filesystem runs slow debugfs commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libext2fs: add quota to libext2fs&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;), we could just rename that function to avoid the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="475045" author="adilger" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2025 17:11:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Li Dongyang (dongyangli@ddn.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38028&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38028&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13241&quot; title=&quot;mount.lustre for large filesystem runs slow debugfs commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: covert to libext2fs for rest of ldiskfs ops&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: d1a62adc3449fe9b16c0adc22f77e99393698afe&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="469368" author="adilger" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2025 21:17:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like setting the filesystem label could be done using &lt;tt&gt;ioctl(FS_IOC_SETFSLABEL)&lt;/tt&gt; for 5.16+ server kernels, and this was backported to el9 as well.  It isn&apos;t clear whether it is worthwhile to backport a patch to ldiskfs to add &lt;tt&gt;FS_IOC_SETFSLABEL&lt;/tt&gt; to el8.x since Lustre 2.16+ defaults to el9 servers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this work should be split into two or three patches:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;new patch to fix e2fsprogs to export the proper headers&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;current patch to use libext2fs calls in &lt;tt&gt;ldiskfs_write_ldd()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;from &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38028&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38028&lt;/a&gt; change &lt;tt&gt;ldiskfs_label_lustre()&lt;/tt&gt; to use &lt;tt&gt;FS_IOC_GETFSLABEL&lt;/tt&gt; iff the filesystem is mounted, instead of opening the filesystem with &lt;tt&gt;libext2fs(EXT2_FLAG_SKIP_MMP)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
